Bugs: If one of your hammer guys gets killed on the way to chop down a tree or repair something, often no one else will follow up the task so areas on the map become blocked. the Android platform, even on a Samsung Galaxy Note 8. It's too easy to 
mistakenly spend your coins on trees that destroy the vagrant camp or just 
as bad sending your builders to their deaths just because you wanted to 
move your King out of harm's way. Another issue is the sh*tty A.I. : Before 
ppl come to the developer's defense, I will say that there are mechanics to 
the game that are challenging to begin with--but they could have improved a 
lot on the overall efficiency of the A.I. Sweeping the issue under the rug 
and saying "well, that's part of what makes the game efficient..". 
No..nooo..just, no.. Too many times.es I've watched units stand idly by

poor excuse for not developing a better A.I. plain and simple. I definitely 
see the potential for the formula of this game.. development just needs to 
be executed much better next time. That is all.

Hello i love your game I also have it on steam and I'm happy to help and support such great game developers such as yourselves. I have one issue and that is there are horizontal lines that come and go at least on my phone can you fix that please and thank you.
Cant find info about saving, is it possible?
Great game. Building, recruiting, defending, upgrading, fighting, exploring what else do you want!

Great game! Love the atmosphere and play style. My biggest gripe (ergo my 4* rating as opposed to a 5) is the framerate hit on my Samsung S5. Granted, not the newest of devices, but not exactly underpowered relatively speaking. Hard to get to grips with the game. If you are a 'turtle' player like me you will have a hard time unfortunately lol. The game really does throw a 'time limit' at you with enemies soon outscaling your defences if you insist on taking too much of a slow and steady approach. A matter of personal preference perhaps, but I would enjoy the game more were I not forced to race against a clock as it were (or at least not as brutally lol).

I wish mobile had more little gem games like this one because that's exactly what it is! "Explore 5 different lands" me: "that'll be easy! Must have a few hours of gameplay" kingdom:new lands : "We packed so much replayability in this bad boy to last ages" *I rejoice* like honestly, it's unfortunate that from the description it's so vague of a game for $10 when in actuality it's a gold mine of a game for the cheap price of $10 smackeroonies. The difficulty and learning curve is perfect. I have told all of my friends about this game because it is the most fun I've had on a game in a very long time. I hope all of you at Raw Fury have a great day, and please keep making games of this caliber because you sure made me happy. I aspire to be a game developer(going to college next year to earn a degree in it) someday, and these are the games I hope I can make soon.
I really like this game, couldn't stop playing forever, I just still don't see 10$ worth of content but if only got to the second island
Not compatible with my 10" Lenovo?? Working so far with ASUS 8"
The game lags a bit, and I think that the controls could be a bit better, but other than those two gripes this game is absolutely amazing

Absolutely fantastic!. Great game the more you play the more you learn! Awsome concept. There are a couple of things, one is its far to easy to drop coin or accidentally cut trees or make things you didnt want!, and so annoying compleating a level only to find out next time you play, your back to the previous level having to complete from a saved area.. Needs a manual save once you get to new island.

Beatiful landscapes great adventures finding secrets and all but 2 things that dog always seems to dissapear and never comeback and 2 i cant pass the 2nd island because when i go back in the game all my progress is lost and it keeps getting annoying plz fix
Can U make a mode where summer lasts forever so we can actually build a big kingdom
love the stunning graphics and fun game style but the only thing that sucks is that the townhall sometimes just stops at his current stage mostly at the stage just before the final stone stage

Extremely pretty but unnecessarily punishing. Far too hard to determine if you're doing well or not. Too many cryptic elements and too easy to die. Can't help feeling this would have been better off not being rogue like.
THIS GAME IS ACTUALLY WORTH BUYING FOR PHONE WHAT!? I didn't know I would ever be ok with buying a phone game until now
Downloaded this as soon as I found this almost flawless game besides controls. I do have one question what does they guy with the mule/donkey do? I give him one coin and he walks away
Confusing at first but very original. Build walls to keep out thieves i guess? Love it!
So good I bought it twice, on Steam and now on Android. Steam version appears to have newer features though.

Love the game! On pc and really happy to see it on android too! Also could you add an optional control sceme with arrows on either side of the screen for movement please. Also maybe some kind of battery saving option?  :)
Absolutely Love this game!
I love this game. Just wanted to say thank you for this gem
It's absolutely a awesome game but it takes some time, so I recommend to do it in your free time.
It's ok but not worth ¬£10 not even worth half that. Repetitive and boring Completed the first quest but feel no desire to continue
My soul is yours
Great, but it lags when switching from night to day, and I'll get an occasional lag spike, but other than that, I loved it on my Xbox and I love it on my phone, props to the devs.

Brilliant, Fun game! The gameplay is relatively simple however the mechanics are challenging and require strategy for every new game! The graphics are amazing for pixel art and the controls are very user friendly!  Definitely worth the price!

It's a great game, love it to pieces, but there's an odd bug where the game seems to lag immensely when the boat is built. There's also silver streaks going horizontally when the Archer statue is enabled, and more random lag. Could be that my device is not very powerful.

positive: looks great   + easy to play with one hand   + challenging (it's not for casuals!) negative: after couple of hours feels repetitive - easy to do mistakes which you can't cancel (start building something) - subjects tend to do stupid stuff and die unnecessarily - performance could be better, later game stages are really slow on LG Nexus  5X  It's a good game, but it's also obvious that it's built for desktop. The price is okay for a desktop game, for mobile it seems to be a bit much. Especially since the gameplay doesn't give too many options. It's quite easy to get to the full developed village and then it's just a numbers game. I'll recommend this game especially for all those hardcore gamers who want to have a fair challenge. You'll need to learn and adapt and then you'll see it's not that hard actually. Balance is a bit off, happens many times that you did some mistakes and realise you can't win anymore, but you won't lose immediately. Once my defense was good enough, but I couldn't get more money -> restart was necessary although the creeps would never kill my people. Feels bad to end a round that way.
No save game option?

Absolutely great game. I saw this on PC but waited for this to be released on mobile as I knew it would make an awesome mobile experience. Gameplay is amazing. It does not hold your hand, but each play through teaches you something knew. The only single flaw is that touching constantly causes dropped coins when my intention is mostly something else like galloping or trying to fill the coin slots when building. Love the pixel art. It keeps me from trying to focus on high graphical detail on a tiny mobil screen. The epitome of a perfect mobile game.
Very good blend of strategy and roguelike difficulty

I bought this game on PC and now I will obsess over it just as much on mobile. Learning the mechanics is the hardest part, but once you start to embrace the fact that you'll learn more from your failures than your successes, you will be able to find an odd sort of pleasure in rebuilding your kingdom with new precious knowledge each time. I love that this game will be a calming and meditative experience in one moment - before turning into a thrilling fight for survival in the next. A beautiful experience.
This game was a fun time killer that interested me not only with its 2D side stroller, but with its innovative story and gameplay that quickly got me into the game and mastering the controls.
One of my favorite games ever. Moody, addictive and immersive. Well worth $12 in an age of crappy click games.
replyContent: Thanks you so much. We'll never put ads or click gimmicks in our games. Also, we'll add new features for free. No paid DLC.

content: An amazing game that catches you off guard. There is so much depth to the game and definitely does not hold your hand as you learn and develop your strategy. A game that you can spend hours at a time on easily. Great game and I look forward to any future entries in this series.
replyContent: So glad you're finding the depth, it's gamers like yourself that motivate us to stick making experiences.

content: Need improvements at controls and Somethimes it lags.
Addictive with a neat atmosphere!  I've only played about an hour but I'm having fun discovering new things and building up my kingdom. I'm impressed that it's the full game like the Steam version.
Great game, but it wont save for me.
replyContent: If you lost the crown that is the experience, it's a roguelike theme of starting over and learning from the past.

content: So I kept asking myself why I would buy a game for $10 on a phone. I still am not quite sure I did. I mean don't get me wrong, the game is beautiful...That's really about it. The gameplay is repetitive and you can work so hard and have it all taken away in minutes. No tutorial or hints at what exactly things do. I guess you just have to figure it out. But then hey, this is a $10 game, why should I? I'd say watch some YouTube videos or something first to see if you'd like it. Maybe the game gets better in the future.
replyContent: Hi Justin, there are 5 lands to explore and unlocks, have you found them all. The game seems repetitive in the beginning but after finding more secrets it can expose a lot of new strategies. Give it a bit more time. And the lack of explanation is intentional to put in the player's hands to figure it out.

content: I love this game! Super addictive and beautiful pixel art. Soundtrack is great too. Definitely worth the money. I put over 40hrs into the PC version. Now excited to have it on mobile.
Good port of an absolutely brilliant PC game.

Nice graphics, nice controls, but the difficulty is hard, ease it up a bit or put a difficulty level like easy, hard etc. Love the game so much, I'm glad you released it on mobile version Keep up the good work raw fury!

Amazing addictive game great rogue like gameplay and town management against monsters. The graphics are beautiful pixelated graphics with great shadows and lighting. I only wish that controls were a little tighter would be much better. Also would like to see this on my PS Vita or PS4 would be much better.  But on my 12  inch Lenovo Yoga this is still amazing.  So addicting.
Fix the control

Good game but I can't get very far. The monsters should give gold and attack every other day. The king/queen should be able to attack. This could be awesome if there were some type of permanent progression. It just sucks to have to start all the way over when I can't get past a week or so. Help us out. Need to be able to upgrade the horse too to be able to sprint further through the map. And the level at which you can upgrade your defenses needs to be dictated by your camp. Also I can't save my progress!
replyContent: There is a roguelike aspect to the game where failing is what should happen while you learn and explore. Also, keep in mind this is the pure game as on PC and Console. So, it's for gamers like you. :)

content: I have played Kingdom: New Lands pretty thoroughly on Steam and was surprised to see that the Android port had finally come out, let alone play well.  It is a solid port from PC! Gratz guys!  --FEEDBACK: Would love to see optional/alternative control layouts. The touch controls work quite well, however the walk/run mechanic is very fidgety and often results in extra time being spent picking up coins I never intended to drop. The same applies to coin spending.  --REQUEST: I would like to see a greater distinction between walk and run. Collecting my sweet sweet tax is much more a chore when I occasionally sprint past my peeps.
replyContent: Good feedback Ash, we'll see what we can do with tuning the touch input.

content: Doesn't support HID controllers.
replyContent: We support a lot of controllers, so can you be more specific. The game uses Rewired in Unity, if you look it up or email us your controller type we'll look into it.

content: I played this for hours with touch support and now I can't play it at all? This is a great game but now it's waste of space on my tablet.  Why would you remove something that was working fine?  Update:  Touch support is back!  Thanks!
replyContent: The game is now update with full touch support for all owners. :)

content: Great game. Very polished. As you play, the difficulty increases, for those that like a challenge. That said, the feature that most ties the game together(in my personal enjoyment) is the amazing soundtrack. The loneliness you feel, as your horse grazes away from safety, is fantastic. You are but a King.
replyContent: Thanks for the review and kind words Alex. :)

content: The touch controls don't work and that annoys me because I have played this game on PC and in the last update on android. This game is fantastic but I wish the touch controls would work since I do not have a controller.
Doesn't work with new nvidia controller!
replyContent:
Update: Full touch support is released now.

This is an issue on Nvidia's side that they are fixing, it is not related to the game. Email us and we'll add you to the Alpha where we're testing touch controls.

content: Its a awesome game that I would definitely recommend to anyone but I feel like being able to direct units would improve it. For instance it was a blood moon and most of my archers were at the side they weren't attacking from if this got added it would definitely be a 5/5

After recent update touch screen controls on my nvidia shield tablet aren't working anymore ... Very disappointing since I really like this game .. I don't want to carry around a controller to play this game.. (Update) Was offered to be in the beta that will be including touch controls. So awesome ! Can't wait :)!
replyContent: Hi Victor, the touch controls were never meant to be there as they were very broken. We will be adding this back in early January and making it playable on any Android device you own. We could also add you to a closed beta to test the touch controls next month.

content: Controller now works thanks to the last update. Giving it 5 stars now.
replyContent: Hi Juan, I emailed you back. We're releasing an update in a few days that should fix 3rd party controller support. Hopefully yours as well.

content: I really want to like this game, but it's very frustrating. Horse needs some kind of stamina indicator. So easy to die because horse will rear up instead of running, and you'll unfairly lose all your progress. Some kind of persistent rewards would be nice. All you do is ride a horse left or right, sprint whenever it decides to let you, and throw coins at stuff. That's it. The nice sounds and decent visuals earn it 3 stars, but this game is not worth the steep $7 price tag. I regret buying this, but maybe it'll get better.
replyContent: Hi Brandon, I suggest watching some Let's Plays on YouTube to show some of the deeper strategies hidden in Kingdom: New Lands. But for a quick tip your horse will breathe heavily when it's about to get tired. I hope you give it a bit more time, there are some cool secrets in the game for you to find. :)

content: Amazing game! It has kept me happy for hours with its unique strategies you can form. My only question is how do I get the giant arrow tower?
replyContent:
Hi Adam,
We're releasing an update in the next few days that allows you to start from any island. As for the ballista tower, do you really want it spoiled for you? :D If you're okay with that check out some of the guides on steam for the game, they're really good. :)

content: This is a cool game with a beautiful art style. My only criticism is that the instructions aren't clear for playing on a tablet. I was able to figure it out (they're simply), but it would be nice if the intro screen was customized for tablet play rather than a controller. For those that don't know, holding the bottom left or right portions of the screen will move the monarch to that direction. Double tapping will make the horse run. Touching the screen above these areas will drop coins. Touching and holding will continue to drop coins (for building/upgrading). Overall, I enjoy this game a lot.
replyContent: Hi Cameron, that is actually a bug. The game only supports playing with a controller for now. We are adding proper touch controls but that won't be ready until early 2017.

content: Great game, very happy to see it land on NVIDIA SHIELD TV!

Needs a lot of work..impossible to progress. Not enough gold to prepare for assaults,not enough recruits to withstand them,recruits miss target ,60% of the time. difficulty curve and mechanics so unbalanced this game becomes extremely unenjoyable to even continue to try..I played 40 rounds with different strategies..beautiful game..shame its broken
replyContent: The game isn't broken, it's the same game as the PC and plenty of people do extremely well. I suggest watching one of the thousands of Let's Plays to learn some awesome strategies to help you improve.

content: Possibly the best game purchase I've ever made in the phone/tablet space. Graphics, music, and gameplay are all absolutely top notch. This studio has just found a new fan in me. Looking forward to see what they do next because this one they knocked out of the park.
replyContent: Thanks Brandon, we have an update releasing soon with some small improvements. In early 2017 we'll also add touch support and all mobile devices it can run on, so if you have other Android devices this purchase will work on both. :)

content: What a fabulous game...   Love the art style but its the gameplay that really shines.  As deep as you want it to be.   Thanks for bringing this to SHIELD ... my new favorite game.
